<h1>About the NWHL Fantasy League</h1>

<h3>About the <a href="http://nwhl.co">NWHL</a></h3>
<p>The National Women's Hockey League, founded in 2015, is the first all-women's paid professional hockey league in the world. It consists of four teams: The Connecticut Whale, the Boston Pride, the New York Riveters, and the Buffalo Beauts. The season consists of 18 weekends of games with a two weekend playoff finishing March 13, 2016. The teams contesting for the Isobel Cup this year are Boston and Buffalo. The athletes on the teams include many American Olympians, college standouts, and hockey players from around the world. Each team has a salary cap, with a league minimum per player salary. Players are also paid a percentage of the revenue from sales of their jerseys.
</p>

