<h3>Denna Laing</h3>
<p>
  On December 31, 2015, the NWHL and the <abbr class="initialism" title="Canadian Women's Hockey League">CWHL</abbr> played an outdoor exhibition game as part of the NHL's Winter Classic in Boston, MA. The NWHL's Boston Blades faced off against the CWHL's Les Canadiennes de Montreal, but many of the <a href="http://www.stanleycupofchowder.com/boston-pride-nwhl/2016/1/15/10775434/how-the-nhl-failed-womens-hockey-at-the-winter-classic">most experienced American players</a> were at USA Hockey's Winter Training Camp. During the course of the game, Boston player Denna Laing <a href="http://nwhl.co/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Update_Denna_Laing_01_08_16_2.pdf">"suffered a significant spinal injury"</a>. Her family is posting <a href="http://dennalaing.org">updates and fundraising information</a> and events supporting her have been held at NWHL and NHL games.
</p>
